  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\nRunning integration tests against our Kovan testnet using Truffle results in the following error:\r\n```\r\nError: The network id specified in the truffle config (69) does not match\r\nthe one returned by the network (1337).  Ensure that both the network \r\nand the provider are properly configured.\r\n```\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. `git clone https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism.git`\r\n1. `git checkout ci/examples` \r\n1. `yarn && yarn build`\r\n1. `cd optimism/examples/Truffle-ERC20-Example`\r\n1. `yarn`\r\n1. Update the `truffle-config-ovm.js` file's `providerOrUrl` field to `https://kovan.optimism.io`\r\n1. `yarn truffle test ./test/erc20.spec.js --network optimistic_ethereum --config truffle-config-ovm.js`\r\n1. See error shown above.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nTests should run successfully and pass (this PR excludes the `eth_estimateGas` issue with l2geth).\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nIf you change the `network_id` to `1337`and re-run the test command, then you will see a different, but still unhelpful error:\r\n```\r\nError: while migrating ERC20: invalid transaction: invalid sender\r\n```",
