    "body": "@platocrat From some brief research, it looks like eth_chainId should be considered the canonical chain ID. network_id and chainId will usually refer to the same value, but they can be differentiated in order to identify specific nodes.\r\n\r\nGood breakdown of distinction:\r\nhttps://besu.hyperledger.org/en/stable/Concepts/NetworkID-And-ChainID/\r\n\r\nHelpful context:\r\nhttps://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-695\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/issues/2163\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/blob/master/EIPS/eip-155.md",
